ive to learning and living the gospel. Owners and managers contract with the university to uphold BYU-Idaho standards and to work with the university in providing students a semester-length contract and help students have a meaningful apartment living experience.</p>
<p><strong>On-Campus</strong></p>
<p>For students of all ages and majors, BYU-Idaho dorms and apartments  provide an ideal atmosphere for learning and growing, with the advantage  of being on-campus. <a href="x9252.xml">Learn more about on-campus housing</a> or<a href="https://web.byui.edu/housingasp"> sign-up today</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Off-Campus</strong></p>
<p>With over 110 different units, off-campus approved housing offers a  variety of styles at competive prices, all participating in helping  students have a   successful and meaninful apartment living experience.  All approved housing units are independently owned and operated but work  closely with the university in an effort to help students have a  meaningful apartment living experience.To learn more   about approved  housing, <a href="x9578.xml">click here</a>.</p>
